(4.5 Operational guardrails before deployment) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(If this model were transitioned beyond coursework, three guardrails would be mandatory.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(First, a monitoring dashboard should track weighted F1, recall \(>50K\), and ECE at a fixed) Tj
0 -14 Td
(cadence, with explicit alert thresholds and a documented owner for intervention. Second,) Tj
0 -14 Td
(subgroup monitoring should use both minimum sample-size rules and confidence intervals to) Tj
0 -14 Td
(avoid over-reacting to noise in very small slices. Third, any threshold revision should be) Tj
0 -14 Td
(logged as a policy change with pre/post impact simulation, not performed ad hoc by) Tj
0 -14 Td
(individual analysts. These controls are simple but materially reduce the risk that a stable) Tj
0 -14 Td
(offline model drifts into unsafe behavior in live use.) Tj
